## 🐞 Issues

### 🔴 High Severity

**1. `isDetectingGenre` is never set to `true` when `songReceiver` was the trigger — now it's set immediately in the coroutine, but it races with the `finally` block of the *previous* job**

In [applyEqForSong](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:183:4-291:5), the new job sets `isDetectingGenre = true` only if `jobId == lastJobId`. But `lastJobId` is incremented *before* the previous job's `finally` block runs. Since the `finally` runs on coroutine cancellation (which is not synchronous), there's a brief window where:
- New job: increments `lastJobId` to N+1, sets `isDetectingGenre = true`
- Old job's `finally`: checks `jobId == lastJobId` → N == N+1 → false → **skips** the reset ✅

This part is actually correct. **However**, if the old job is *already past the jobId check* inside the `finally` before cancellation propagates, `isDetectingGenre` could be set to `false` incorrectly. This is the residual race.

**2. Orphaned [handlePlaybackStateChange](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:159:4-170:5) method (lines 160–171)**

This method is defined but **never called** anywhere in the file. The broadcasts that used to call it were removed. If [observeState()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:77:4-109:5) doesn't fully replicate its behavior (it mostly does, but see issue #3), this dead code is a maintenance hazard and indicates incomplete cleanup.

**3. [observeState()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:77:4-109:5) — playback flow does NOT re-trigger genre detection on playback start after a skip**

When a song is skipped, `SongState.currentSong` is updated → [observeState](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:77:4-109:5) triggers [handleSongChange](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:172:4-181:5). But the song collector **only fires if `title != lastProcessedTitle`**. If the user pauses and resumes the same song, `isPlaying` changes but `lastProcessedTitle` hasn't changed, so [forceReapply()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:149:4-157:5) is called via the `isPlaying` flow. This is mostly fine — **but [forceReapply()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:149:4-157:5) calls [applyEqForSong](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:183:4-291:5) which may hit the deduplication guard** at line 188 and return early if the same song title/artist is already processed. This means **resuming playback after a pause may sometimes not reapply EQ**.

**4. [onNotificationRemoved](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/SongDetectionService.kt:58:4-80:5) still sends a `PLAYBACK_STATE_CHANGED` broadcast (lines 75–79)**

After removing all other broadcasts, this one is still present. Since [AudioEngineServiceLocal](cci:2://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:34:0-369:1) no longer registers a `BroadcastReceiver`, **this broadcast is sent to nobody**. The `isPlaying` flow is already set to `false` immediately above (line 73), so the engine's flow collector will respond. The orphaned broadcast is harmless but wasteful and logically inconsistent.

**5. [handleSongChange](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:172:4-181:5) (line 173) — calls `eqEngine.reinitialize()` synchronously on Main thread**

