### 🟡 Medium Severity

**6. `wasLastJobDebounced` deduplication logic is inverted / confusing**

```kotlin
if (currentSongJob?.isActive == true && lastProcessedTitle == title && lastProcessedArtist == artist) {
    if (debounce || !wasLastJobDebounced) { return }
}
```

This means: "if same song is in flight AND (new request is debounced OR last job was also immediate), ignore." The intent is to allow an *immediate* request to cancel an in-flight *debounced* one. But a side effect is: **two rapid [forceReapply()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:149:4-157:5) calls for the same song will both be silently dropped** if the job is already active. This can cause EQ to not update after a preference change like intensity if the song hasn't changed.

