## ⚡ Performance Notes

- **Room DB is instantiated without `.allowMainThreadQueries()` and used on IO — correct.** But the database is built on [onCreate](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:50:4-62:5) every time the service restarts. Consider a singleton pattern (`companion object` or injected via `Application`).
- **`withTimeoutOrNull(15000)` wraps the entire DB + network path.** The DB query is fast (`<100ms`), so spending 15s waiting on it being included in the timeout is acceptable but slightly imprecise. Per-operation timeouts would be cleaner.
- **[createNotification()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:337:4-363:5) is called on every [updateNotification()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:365:4-368:5)**, which recreates the `NotificationChannel` on every call (though Android no-ops this on subsequent calls, it's unnecessary overhead).
- **[observePreferences()](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:111:4-135:5) launches 6 separate coroutines** — minor, but could be consolidated using `combine()` for the custom tuning/auto-EQ flows that both trigger [forceReapply](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Audix/app/src/main/java/com/audix/app/service/AudioEngineServiceLocal.kt:149:4-157:5).

